dnl Find the compiler and linker flags for the blacklist library on
dnl FreeBSD which integrates with the blacklistd daemon.
dnl
dnl Finds the compiler and linker flags for linking with the blacklist
dnl library.
dnl Provides the --with-blacklist, --with-blacklist-lib, and
dnl --with-blacklist-include configure options to specify non-standard
dnl paths to the blacklist library.
dnl
dnl Provides the macro INN_LIB_BLACKLIST and sets the substitution
dnl variables BLACKLIST_CPPFLAGS, BLACKLIST_LDFLAGS, and BLACKLIST_LIBS.
dnl Also provides INN_LIB_BLACKLIST_SWITCH to set CPPFLAGS, LDFLAGS, and
dnl LIBS to include the blacklist library, saving the current values first,
dnl and INN_LIB_BLACKLIST_RESTORE to restore those settings to before the
dnl last INN_LIB_BLACKLIST_SWITCH. Defines HAVE_BLACKLIST and sets
dnl inn_use_BLACKLIST to true.
dnl
dnl Provides the INN_LIB_BLACKLIST_OPTIONAL macro, which should be used if
dnl blacklist support is optional. This macro will still always set the
dnl substitution variables, but they'll be empty if libblacklist is not
dnl found or if --without-blacklist is given.  Defines HAVE_BLACKLIST and
dnl sets inn_use_BLACKLIST to true if the blacklist library is found and
dnl --without-blacklist is not given.
dnl
dnl Depends on the lib-helper.m4 framework.
